                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15367132" author="jahewson" created="Fri, 8 Jul 2016 02:50:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So the code in getFallbackFontName in FontMapperImpl is looking for &quot;Windings-Roman&quot;. The question is whether &quot;-Regular&quot; is a popular postfix or just something specific to Windings (because it&apos;s a symbol font, not a roman font). I&apos;m thinking it&apos;s probably the latter, so we could special-case it in getFallbackFontName.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15367138" author="jahewson" created="Fri, 8 Jul 2016 02:56:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Alternatively, because we know that Windings-Regular is actually Windings, and not a fallback, we could modify findFont to try adding &quot;-Regular&quot; to the base name. That way the font mapping won&apos;t incorrectly count as a fallback.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15367246" author="tilman" created="Fri, 8 Jul 2016 05:32:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What I did is to add it to that mapping list for the Standard 14 fonts.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15367844" author="jahewson" created="Fri, 8 Jul 2016 15:49:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That works but it&apos;s not the right fix. Windings isn&apos;t a standard 14 font so it doesn&apos;t belong in that list. We don&apos;t want other hardcoded mappings there.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15500873" author="lehmi" created="Sun, 18 Sep 2016 12:04:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve extended the findFont method as proposed and everything works fine (see attached patch). &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Should we limit the additional &quot;-Regular&quot;-postfix to the &quot;Wingding&quot;-font or does it make sense to append that postfix to every fontname?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15500929" author="tilman" created="Sun, 18 Sep 2016 12:42:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I just tested your patch without the &quot;if&quot; and it makes no differences except for the file that is central to this issue. I&apos;m on Windows 7.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15504000" author="jira-bot" created="Mon, 19 Sep 2016 16:58:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1761484 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=lehmi&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;lehmi&quot;&gt;lehmi&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/branches/2.0&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1761484&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1761484&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-3412&quot; title=&quot;Using fallback font &amp;#39;TimesNewRomanPSMT&amp;#39; for &amp;#39;Wingdings&amp;#39;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-3412&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-3412&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: append &quot;-Regular&quot; to fonts when searching for non-embedded fonts&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15504006" author="jira-bot" created="Mon, 19 Sep 2016 16:59:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1761485 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=lehmi&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;lehmi&quot;&gt;lehmi&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1761485&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1761485&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-3412&quot; title=&quot;Using fallback font &amp;#39;TimesNewRomanPSMT&amp;#39; for &amp;#39;Wingdings&amp;#39;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-3412&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-3412&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: append -Regular to fonts when searching for non-embedded fonts&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15504012" author="lehmi" created="Mon, 19 Sep 2016 17:02:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve added the patch as proposed but without the if-clause.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt; Thanks for testing!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15504302" author="jahewson" created="Mon, 19 Sep 2016 18:47:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Trying the postfix for all fonts is preferred. Because Windings isn&apos;t a base-14 font we&apos;d prefer not to special-case it if possible.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15504311" author="jahewson" created="Mon, 19 Sep 2016 18:49:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The current state looks good - it&apos;s a general-purpose fix rather than Windings-specific, so we might even improve the situation for other fonts using the &quot;-Regular&quot; postfix. Nice.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
